TP   Domain
CC   This entry represents a C-terminal domain (approximately 142-170
CC   residues, positions 772-943) found in PelA, a glycoside hydrolase
CC   family 114 protein involved in Pel exopolysaccharide biosynthesis.
CC   This domain follows the glycoside hydrolase 114 domain
CC   (Pfam:PF03537). PelA modifies the Pel exopolysaccharide, which is
CC   important for biofilm formation in Pseudomonas aeruginosa and related
CC   bacteria. The family is found in Pseudomonadota, particularly in
CC   Betaproteobacteria (Burkholderiaceae, Burkholderiales),
CC   Gammaproteobacteria, and Alphaproteobacteria.
RN   [1]
RM   40120681
RT   Structural and functional analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa PelA
RT   provides insight into the modification of the Pel exopolysaccharide.
RA   Van Loon JC, Le Mauff F, Vargas MA, Gilbert S, Pfoh R, Morrison ZA,
RA   Razvi E, Nitz M, Sheppard DC, Howell PL;
RL   J Biol Chem 2025;301:108432.
